oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Elise Croft and friend posing as a couple in love
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of an unidentified young woman and Elise Croft dressed up in fancy clothes pose as a couple. The unidentified woman is dressed in a man's suit and top hat with a cane, while Elise is in a long white dress. "Friday - November 18 - 1911-, 26 F. St." is written on the scrapbook page.
This is the first of two houses the Crofts owned in Havana and was located at 26 F Street in Vedado. The second house was located at the corner of 19 and F Streets, Vedado.
